<examples>
The following examples illustrate the expected level of rigour and the tone of a well-formed estimation. They are reference outputs from past projects; do not copy their numbers, use them only as a calibration anchor.

<example>
<project_description>
A small B2B SaaS to manage employee equipment loans (laptops, headsets). Single tenant per customer, role-based access for HR and IT, audit trail of every loan, weekly email digest. No mobile app.
</project_description>
<estimation>
| phase            | duration_weeks | cost_eur | confidence_pct |
|------------------|----------------|----------|----------------|
| Discovery        | 1              | 2,500    | 85             |
| Design           | 1              | 2,000    | 80             |
| Implementation   | 5              | 14,500   | 70             |
| QA               | 1              | 2,000    | 75             |
| Launch           | 1              | 1,500    | 80             |

Totals: 360 total_hours, 22,500 total_cost_eur, 9 total_duration_weeks.
Team: 1 product designer (part-time), 1 backend developer, 1 full-stack developer.
</estimation>
</example>

<example>
<project_description>
Native mobile app (iOS + Android) for a meal-prep startup: catalogue browsing, weekly subscription, payment via Stripe, push notifications, and a delivery tracking screen wired to an existing logistics API.
</project_description>
<estimation>
| phase            | duration_weeks | cost_eur | confidence_pct |
|------------------|----------------|----------|----------------|
| Discovery        | 2              | 4,500    | 80             |
| Design           | 3              | 7,500    | 75             |
| Implementation   | 9              | 32,500   | 65             |
| QA               | 2              | 5,000    | 70             |
| Launch           | 1              | 2,500    | 80             |

Totals: 800 total_hours, 52,000 total_cost_eur, 17 total_duration_weeks.
Team: 1 designer, 2 mobile developers (one per platform), 1 backend developer (part-time), 1 QA engineer.
</estimation>
</example>

<example>
<project_description>
Internal tool to centralise marketing assets across three brands: search, tagging, role-based access for marketing and legal, and an approval workflow before assets become public.
</project_description>
<estimation>
| phase            | duration_weeks | cost_eur | confidence_pct |
|------------------|----------------|----------|----------------|
| Discovery        | 1              | 2,500    | 85             |
| Design           | 2              | 4,000    | 80             |
| Implementation   | 6              | 18,000   | 70             |
| QA               | 1              | 2,500    | 75             |
| Launch           | 1              | 1,500    | 80             |

Totals: 460 total_hours, 28,500 total_cost_eur, 11 total_duration_weeks.
Team: 1 designer (part-time), 1 backend developer, 1 frontend developer.
</estimation>
</example>
</examples>
